This paper discusses the metrics commonly used for analyzing, developing, and managing telecommunication networks. It covers a broad range of topics related to telecommunication systems, including energy and power metrics, quality-of-service metrics, quality-of-experience metrics, security metrics, and reliability and resilience metrics. Given the focus on networking and communication systems, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). However, the paper also touches on security and software engineering aspects, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of metrics in system design and operation, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-categories.
